[[File:Entrance to Dominion Park Montreal 1910.jpg|thumb|Entrance to Dominion Park, 1910]] '''Dominion Park''' was an [[amusement park]] in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada, situated between [[Notre-Dame Street]] (near Haig Avenue) and the [[Saint Lawrence River]] in the early twentieth century. The park opened on June 2, 1906 and was shuttered in 1937, surviving two fires, in 1913 and 1919. It was owned by the [[Montreal Suburban Tramway and Power]] company.
==See also== *[[Belmont Park, Montreal]]
